---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ExpediaWidget from '../components/ExpediaWidget.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | The Trails of Ceylon — Sri Lanka Travel Guide"
  description="The Trails of Ceylon is an independent travel resource dedicated entirely to Sri Lanka. Learn about our mission, editorial approach and what we cover."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative h-[50vh] min-h-[360px] overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="/images/heroes/hero-sigiriya.webp"
      alt="Sigiriya rock fortress Sri Lanka"
      class="w-full h-full object-cover object-center"
      loading="eager"
      fetchpriority="high"
      width="1440"
      height="810"
      style="object-fit:cover;"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 via-black/30 to-transparent"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 p-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1 class="font-serif font-black text-white text-5xl sm:text-6xl mb-3">About Us</h1>
        <p class="text-white/80 text-xl">The independent Sri Lanka travel resource</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats -->
  <section class="bg-ceylon-green-900 py-10">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-6 text-center">
        {[
          { value: '35+',  label: 'Destinations Covered' },
          { value: '26+',  label: 'Activity Guides' },
          { value: '10+',  label: 'Travel Planning Guides' },
          { value: '8',    label: 'UNESCO World Heritage Sites' },
        ].map(stat => (
          <div>
            <p class="font-serif font-black text-ceylon-gold-400 text-4xl">{stat.value}</p>
            <p class="text-ceylon-green-200 text-sm mt-1">{stat.label}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main content -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none prose-headings:font-serif prose-headings:text-ceylon-green-800 prose-a:text-ceylon-green-700 prose-strong:text-gray-900">

        <h2>Welcome to The Trails of Ceylon</h2>
        <p>The Trails of Ceylon is an independent travel resource dedicated entirely to Sri Lanka — one of the world's most extraordinary yet underrated destinations. Our mission is simple: to help travellers discover, plan and experience the very best that this remarkable island has to offer.</p>
        <p>Sri Lanka has everything — ancient ruins, misty highlands, golden beaches, incredible wildlife and some of the world's most vibrant food culture — all packed into a compact island you can explore in any direction. Yet despite all of this, it remains refreshingly uncrowded and genuinely affordable compared to many other tropical destinations.</p>
        <p>We built The Trails of Ceylon because we felt the island deserved a dedicated, beautifully designed and genuinely useful travel resource — one that goes beyond the typical tourist trail and helps visitors experience Sri Lanka at its very best.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Train banner image -->
  <div class="w-full h-64 sm:h-80 overflow-hidden">
    <img
      src="/images/heroes/hero-train.webp"
      alt="Scenic highland railway Sri Lanka"
      class="w-full h-full object-cover object-center"
      loading="lazy"
      width="1440"
      height="810"
      style="object-fit:cover;"
    />
  </div>

  <!-- More content -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none prose-headings:font-serif prose-headings:text-ceylon-green-800 prose-a:text-ceylon-green-700 prose-strong:text-gray-900">

        <h2>What We Cover</h2>
        <p>Our team of Sri Lanka travel writers and researchers covers every corner of the island:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>35+ destination guides</strong> — from Sigiriya to Jaffna, Ella to Arugam Bay</li>
          <li><strong>26+ activity guides</strong> — wildlife safaris, whale watching, surfing, hiking and more</li>
          <li><strong>Complete travel planning guides</strong> — visas, budgets, itineraries, getting around</li>
          <li><strong>Honest blog articles</strong> — tips, stories and insider advice</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Our Editorial Approach</h2>
        <p>Every piece of content on The Trails of Ceylon is thoroughly researched and written with the traveller's best interests in mind. We are committed to:</p>

        <p><strong>Accuracy</strong> — We keep our guides up to date with current prices, opening hours and travel conditions.</p>
        <p><strong>Honesty</strong> — We tell you what's worth your time and money — and what isn't.</p>
        <p><strong>Responsibility</strong> — We promote ethical wildlife experiences, sustainable tourism and respect for local communities and culture.</p>
        <p><strong>Practicality</strong> — Real, actionable information that helps you actually plan your trip — not just inspire you.</p>

        <h2>How We Make Money</h2>
        <p>The Trails of Ceylon is free to use and always will be. We keep the lights on through:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Affiliate commissions</strong> — when you book hotels or tours through our links, we earn a small commission at no extra cost to you</li>
          <li><strong>Display advertising</strong> — carefully selected ads that don't compromise your reading experience</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We only recommend products and services we genuinely believe offer good value for travellers. Our editorial content is never influenced by commercial relationships.</p>

        <h2>Get In Touch</h2>
        <p>Have a question about Sri Lanka? Found an error in one of our guides? Want to work with us?</p>
        <p>We'd love to hear from you — <a href="/contact/">get in touch here</a>.</p>

      </div>

      <!-- Values -->
      <div class="mt-16 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 not-prose">
        {[
          { title: 'Honest',      body: 'We tell you the truth — even if that means saying a famous attraction is overrated.' },
          { title: 'Responsible', body: 'We promote ethical wildlife experiences and sustainable tourism practices.' },
          { title: 'Practical',   body: 'Real, actionable information — not vague inspiration. We help you actually plan your trip.' },
        ].map(val => (
          <div class="text-center bg-ceylon-green-50 border border-ceylon-green-100 rounded-2xl p-6">
            <h3 class="font-serif font-bold text-ceylon-green-800 text-lg mb-2">{val.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">{val.body}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ExpediaWidget heading="✈️ Search Hotels & Flights to Sri Lanka" />
</BaseLayout>
